pageContext.claim: “And frankly, uh, that's turning out to be as big a story as the corruption itself. They are trying to protect him because that's the way it is with the Democrats. It's a part of the Democrat Party, I guess. But they're trying to protect Biden from this corruption where they got caught.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump falsely claims that fact checks placed by social-media companies, pointing out his falsehoods, is a form of rigging the election. Twitter also made it difficult to circulate the New York Post article on Hunter Biden's laptop because it was unverified.
